    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> Aug. 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1778.</dateline>
                <salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I am much obliged to you for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> favor. My enquiry
                    after <persName ref="pe0090">Lord Fife’s</persName> pedigree was mere private
                    curiosity having heard some singular anecdotes concerning it. I hope <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low’s</persName>
                    <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0058">journal</title></bibl> has reached
                    you for I sent it a month ago to <persName ref="pe0043">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Cadel</persName>. <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> need not be very precipitate for the complection
                    of the Times are far from favorable to authors any more than the public. I
                    truely lament our approaching loss in <persName ref="pe0022">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Ramsay</persName>; but shall rejoice in better
                    news.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>your faithful humble
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed></closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>I fear <persName ref="pe0104">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gough</persName> is
                        ill not having heard from him this long time.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p><address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Custom house.</addrLine>
                    </address></p>
            </div>
        </body>
